                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <head>446. Telegram 1369 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d446fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/1–1356.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-01-13"
                            >January 13, 1956, 2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d446-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d446-1"/>
                <p>1369. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Lai Ya-Li (Matthews 3776, 7225, 3920) and <persName>Wang Pao-Liu</persName>
                    (7037, 4946, 4080) respectively, replaced Li and Lin on CHICOM Ambassadorial
                    delegation yesterday. Request biographic information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
